{{Quote|We specifically asked the Jedi stay out of this, since we were confident we could handle this. It's a Gotal issue, best handled by Gotal.|[[Shagrad Loset]]|<ref name="Standoff" />}}
The '''Gotal Foreign Affairs Commune''' was part of the government of [[Antar 4/Legends|Antar 4]], the homeworld of the [[Gotal/Legends|Gotals]].<ref name="Guerrillas">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|52|regional/13418_4.html|Gotal Guerillas Hijack Commuter Hopper, Take Hostages}}</ref>

Though the natural empathy and consequent near-anarchy in Gotal society meant that Antar 4 did not have a single head of government or spokesperson,<ref name="Guerrillas" /> a Gotal named [[Shagrad Loset]] did act as the leader of the Gotal Foreign Affairs Commune during the [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|Separatist Crisis]] of [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].<ref name="Standoff">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|53|jediwatch/13425_1.html|Gotal Standoff Ends Violently}}</ref>

During the [[Gotal hostage standoff]] on [[Atzerri/Legends|Atzerri]], when [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]]-aligned Gotals from the [[Roshu Sune/Legends|Roshu Sune]] militant group took several hostages, including Gotal [[Emissary/Legends|Emissary]] [[Nathanjo Nirrelz]], the Gotal Foreign Affairs Commune attempted to resolve the crisis on their own. They tried to dissuade the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] from intervening, and refused to cooperate with the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] taskforce led by [[Sarrissa Jeng/Legends|Sarrissa Jeng]].<ref name="Guerrillas" /> The Jedi did not wait for the Commune's diplomatic efforts, and began negotiations themselves. After the negotiations were cut short by [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] fire, several hostages and all of the hijackers ended up dead. Loset blamed the Jedi and their "[[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] diplomacy" for the standoff's violent end, expressing the opinion that the Gotals could have handled the standoff better themselves.<ref name="Standoff" />

